cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.MM 

This paper deals with unsupervised domain adaptation for 3D semantic segmentation using multi-modal data, specifically 2D images and 3D point clouds. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel approach for learning from multi-modality, which involves mutual mimicking and disentanglement, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The application of the proposed method is in autonomous driving, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also involves the use of deep learning techniques, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper deals with multi-modal data, which is a subfield of multimedia (cs.MM).
